#: ../../N/Nathan-Hale.rst:5
msgid "Nathan Hale"
msgstr "Nathan Hale"

#: ../../N/Nathan-Hale.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../N/Nathan-Hale.rst:9
msgid ""
"An asterisk (see also :ref:`splat`\\, :ref:`ASCII`\\). Oh, you want an "
"etymology? Notionally, from \"I regret that I have only one asterisk for my "
"country! \", a misquote of the famous remark uttered by Nathan Hale just "
"before he was hanged. Hale was a (failed) spy for the rebels in the American"
" War of Independence."
msgstr ""
"アスタリスク(\\ :ref:`splat`\\ 、\\ :ref:`ASCII`\\ も参照)。おや、語源が知りたいって? "
"観念的には、「我が祖国に捧げるアスタリスクが一つしかないのが残念だ!」という、Nathan "
"Haleが絞首刑にされる直前に発した有名な言葉の誤った引用から。Haleはアメリカ独立戦争における反乱軍の(失敗した)スパイだった。"
